{
  "name": "Crown Chamber",
  "description": "# The Crown Chamber — Netherese Ruins\n\nThe innermost chamber of the Netherese ruins, where the seven crown fragments converge. This vast circular chamber was once the heart of a floating Netherese enclave, and its architecture still bears traces of the magic that once kept it aloft.\n\n## Chamber Features\n- **Seven Pedestals** — Arranged in a heptagon, each pedestal holds a slot for a crown fragment\n- **Arcane Runes** — Glowing runes cover the floor and walls, pulsing with residual Netherese magic\n- **Floating Shards** — Seven crystalline shards hover above the central dais, slowly rotating\n- **Reality Warping** — The air shimmers with distorted light, hinting at the crown's reality-warping power\n- **Valandril's Throne** — A skeletal throne of black stone sits at the chamber's eastern end\n\n## Tactical Considerations\n- The chamber is large enough to accommodate 12 level-20 characters and their enemies\n- The seven pedestals can be used strategically — placing a fragment on a pedestal triggers different effects\n- The floating shards provide cover (half-cover) and can be destroyed to release arcane energy\n- The reality-warping effect creates unpredictable environmental hazards each round",
